Belarusian Language Module for datetime2 Package

Author: Mikalai Keida

Licence: LPPL

Required Packages: datetime2, tracklang

Example usage:

\documentclass{article}
\usepackage[belarusian]{datetime2}
\begin{document}
\today
\end{document}

\documentclass[belarusian]{article}
\usepackage{babel}
\usepackage[useregional]{datetime2}
\begin{document}
\today
\end{document}

\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{polyglossia}
\setmainlanguage{belarusian}
\usepackage[belarusian]{datetime2}
\begin{document}
\today
\end{document}

INSTALLATION
============

xelatex datetime2-belarusian.ins

Move all *.ldf files to
TEXMF/tex/latex/datetime2-contrib/datetime2-belarusian/

Documentation:

xelatex datetime2-belarusian.dtx
makeindex -s gind.ist datetime2-belarusian.idx
makeindex -s gglo.ist -o datetime2-belarusian.gls datetime2-belarusian.glo
xelatex datetime2-belarusian.dtx
xelatex datetime2-belarusian.dtx

Move datetime2-belarusian.pdf and README to
TEXMF/doc/latex/datetime2-contrib/datetime2-belarusian/

